%% Diagram: Hedged Request Timing (Dean & Barroso, 2013)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant A as Replica A (primary)
    participant B as Replica B (hedge)

    Note over C, B: hedgingDelay = p95 latency budget

    C->>A: request (t = 0)
    activate A
    Note over A: GC pause / cold cache /\nhot shard - slow this time

    Note over C: t = p95 - primary still pending\nfire the hedge
    C->>B: duplicate request (t = p95)
    activate B

    B-->>C: response (t = p95 + median)
    deactivate B
    Note over C: first response wins
    C--xA: cancel primary
    deactivate A

    Note over C, B: Trigger at p95 keeps the extra\nload at roughly 5 percent of requests\nwhile collapsing the p99/p99.9 tail.
    Note over C, B: gRFC A6: an RPC may have a\nretryPolicy OR a hedgingPolicy,\nnever both at the same time.
